HEADWORD: Phonolite
<hw>Pho"no*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Phono-</ets>
+ <ets>-lite</ets>: cf. F. <ets>phonolithe</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A compact, feldspathic, igneous rock containing
nephelite, ha⟦uum⟧ynite, etc. Thin slabs give a ringing sound when
struck; -- called also <altname>clinkstone</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

